<plot>Beauty is in the eye of the beholder and science now allows people to share their vision of beauty with the rest of the world. Already, these advancements are providing everyday people with unprecedented access to choice. From cosmetic surgery to egg donation to the mapping of the human genome, science is engineering a future of designer genes and custom-made children. In 2005 alone, over 1 million people in America underwent cosmetic surgery- an all time record. But as pioneering technology breaks evolution down to a science, one question still remains unanswered: in a Perfect World, will you make the cut?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?014441</url></doc>
